<section>
  <title>Inside the Box</title>
  <para>The BlipBox consists of a few simple elements cleverly put together. At the core there is a 10x8 matrix of super-bright LED's with individually adjustable brightness. Overlaying this is a precision touch screen. On the side you will find some more controls; in the current incarnation there is one button and one knob.</para>
  <para>The box plugs straight into a computer's USB port. Being bus-powered, it doesn't require batteries or power adaptor.</para>
  <para>The current prototypes use an <ulink url="http://www.arduino.cc">arduino</ulink> board which has an ATMega168 microprocessor and USB connection. We are planning to provide DIY kits quite soon, allowing anyone to build their own box.</para>
</section>
 
